Interface TaskResponse

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
DeletionImpl, NotificationImpl, TaskResponseImpl
public interface TaskResponse
extends PlanningDirective

TaskResponse interface is the base interface of responses to a task that was sent to an agent and serves to identify the task. The Notification and Deletion responses extend this interface.

getChildTaskUID

UID getChildTaskUID()
Get the child task's UID that was disposed. It's parent task is identified by getTaskUID(); Useful for keeping track of which subtask of an Expansion caused the re-aggregation of the Expansion's reported allocationresult.

Returns:
UID
